item.title: Kind World Presents: Endless Thread's look into "Aunties:" abortion access advocates of Reddit
item.description: Kind World presents Endless Thread's look into Reddit'sÂ Auntie Network, an online community "dedicated to providing information and resources to those in need of abortion services." It has been inundated with new members since the Supreme Court's decision to overturn Roe v. Wade was leaked in early May. Community members offer rides, lodging, and emotional support for those seeking abortion. Feed: https://rss.wbur.org/kindworld/podcast
